Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on resource allocation for device-to-device communication in cellular networks, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with maximizing network throughput and achieving higher spectral efficiency, which are key objectives of information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a robust distributed solution for resource allocation, which involves control and optimization of network resources. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper considers quality-of-service requirements for cellular and D2D user equipments, which are relevant to multimedia applications. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although the paper does not explicitly deal with cryptography and security, resource allocation is a critical aspect of secure communication and can be relevant to this sub-category.
